description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at Leicestershire Partnership NHS Trust whereby we are seeking an individual to assist the clinical category team within this large non-acute Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have the ambition to become a best in class, non-acute procurement team, following best practice, national initiatives, and seeking proactive collaborations. In order for us to achieve this, we are looking for bright, enthusiastic and dynamic individuals to join the LPT procurement team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our drive to meet our strategic objectives around ‘Ensuring Sustainability’ we are seeking a procurement professional with the skills and determination to make a real difference when it comes to supporting the Trust’s transactional procurement function. This is an exciting opportunity for someone who has proven transactional buying and eProcurement experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to support all Trust buying processes, provide a procurement helpdesk, understand public sector procurement rules and regulations, and be able to negotiate with suppliers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be based at County Hall, Glenfield, Leicester and the applicant will need to be comfortable with home-working in the current climate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agile Working&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recognise the need to develop modern working practices to enable employees to maximise their performance and productivity whilst maintaining a good work life balance. To this aim the Trust has adopted an Agile working methodology as outlined within the Trust Agile working Policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post advertised falls under the Trust’s Agile working methodology, so if successful you will be appointed as an Agile Worker, and will need to work to the Trusts Agile working policy. Talk to the recruiting manager about what this means in practice for you.&lt;/p&gt;
